cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper deals with analyzing the information embedded in discrete-valued stochastic time series, which involves information theory and machine learning concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of multivariate information measures, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also talks about the uncertainty of a single observation, which is a topic of interest in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the scaling of measures with the length of the time window, which is a topic of interest in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper talks about the need to build models, which is a topic of interest in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
